text: Catherine Clara LaMore (July 2, 1926 â€“ April 2, 2021), also known by her married name Clara Walker, was an American competition swimmer who represented the United States at the 1948 Summer Olympics in London. LaMore competed at the women's 200-meter breaststroke and recorded a time of 3:23.6. LaMore was born in Providence, Rhode Island.
